# Pem — Inbox UI shell

## Layers

1. **Shell** — Inbox-style list chrome: header (search + settings), **segmented tabs** (Preps / Prepping / Archived — icon + label in a tinted track with active pill, same pattern as the old `HomeTabDock` segment), borderless rows + hairlines, amber signals. Colors come from **`ThemeContext`** + **`segmentTrackTint`** (`homeLayout.ts`) — **light and dark** match the rest of the app.
2. **Cards** — Rich prep experiences live on **detail** (`/prep/[id]`). Old `/bundle/[id]` URLs redirect to the same prep route.

## Pem constraints (do not violate)

- **Dump is text-only** — no voice UI, no mic as default input; **`/dump`** is the text composer. Do not add voice recording or “voice default” sheets from older specs.
- **No FlashList** in repo unless a dependency is added — prefer **`FlatList`**.

## What’s implemented vs roadmap

| Area | Status |
|------|--------|
| Theme-aware shell (`useInboxShell`) + header + top tabs + FAB | Yes |
| `PrepInboxRow` (Gmail-style) | Yes |
| Unread-first sort on **Inbox** tab | Yes |
| **Done** tab (dimmed rows; `PATCH /preps/:id/done`) | Yes |
| Swipe archive / delete / restore (`HubSwipeableRow`) | Yes |
| Full-screen search overlay, FlashList, multi-select, “mark unread” swipe | Not yet — needs UX + API for unread |

**Mark unread** swipe requires a backend way to clear `opened_at` (or equivalent); until then do not fake it.

## Styling rules

- List rows: **no** card border/shadow in the scroll; **hairline** separators with **left indent** (~60px from spec).
- **Amber left strip** = in-progress prep on Prepping tab (`PrepInboxRow`).
- **Bold title + bright text** = unread ready prep; `ApiPrep.opened_at` drives `prep.unread`.
- **FAB** — `InboxDumpFab` → `router.push("/dump")` bottom-right.

## Deprecated / unused

- **`HomeTabDock`** (bottom segmented + mic) was replaced by **top `InboxShellTabBar`** + **`InboxDumpFab`**. Keep file until fully removed; do not wire it back on `home` without an explicit product decision.
